    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>University of Witten/Herdecke</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to develop and implement evidence-based and family-oriented
      support for young carers and their families in Germany. Hypothesis is that families' own
      support mechanisms, combined with externally provided support that is determined by the
      families' specific needs, will help to overcome their burden and enable families to live in
      the way they wish to despite chronic illness. This will lead to a measurable increase in
      HRQOL of children concerned.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
